6. Behavioral Intelligence Layer



Adaptive Friction Engine:

Dynamically adjusts intervention intensity based on relapse patterns.

Trigger Mapping:

Users log emotional triggers (bored, stressed, lonely, avoiding work).

Dashboard correlates mood with screen behavior.

Micro Reflection Prompts:

End-of-day reflection questions.

Monthly behavior pattern summaries.

Distraction Journal:

Users log what they were avoiding.

Digital Clarity Score:

Composite behavioral metric combining streaks, mood stability, and focus consistency.


---

7. Academic Productivity Layer



Pomodoro Focus Timer:

Tagged by subject (e.g., Math, Programming, GATE prep).

Exam Countdown Widget:

Displays days remaining and recommended study hours.

Quick Notes Vault:

Offline markdown notes system.

Virtual Study Rooms:

Group timed focus sessions.

Visible participation count.

Subject Analytics Dashboard:

Weekly subject-hour distribution.


